@NODE History "History"
V37.181  (v1.81)

  o First release

V37.182  (v1.82) Not Released

  o If there was a blank line at the end of the temp file, ToolType would
    report an error reading the temp file. (fixed)
  o Blank lines can be entered anywhere, they will just be ignored.
  o Forgot to close the Icon Library (fixed)

V37.183  (v1.83)  First release to Fred Fish.

  o Increased limit on number of tooltypes to 256.
  o Cleaned up code a bit.

v37.190  (v1.90) Not released

  o Now uses ReadArgs for cli interface
  o If user did not have the %s in the editor name, tooltype would not
    be able to load the tempfile.  Now if %s is missing it will be appended.
  o Includes Installer script that allows automatic configuration.
  o If one of the libraries failed to open, the others were not closed.
    (fixed)

v37.194  (v1.94)

  o Now the commented tooltypes can be placed after the active ones when
    sorting.
  o Optimized code making the executable smaller.

v37.195  (v1.95)

  o Did not realize the drawer icons had tooltypes, now you can edit those too
    (Reported by Peter Augustin)
  o Fixed the enforcer hit with icons that had no tooltypes.
    (Thanks to Preben Nielsen for explaining how)
  o Will now look for ENV:EDITOR before looking for ENV:TOOLTYPE.  That way if
    you have EDITOR set for more, ToolType will also use it.
    (Suggested by Preben Nielsen)

v37.196 (v1.96) Not released

  o Tempfile has been renamed to T:TT_<iconname>.temp<x>, to make it easier to
    know which icon your editing.
  o ToolType would put the first tooltype at the begining and again at the end
    when sorting if there were no commented tooltypes. (fixed)

v37.201 (v2.1) Not released

  o Now has an optional appicon that can be started from WB or Shell.
    (Suggested by Greg Gerke)
  o If the filerequester was canceled, the allocated memory was not returned
    (fixed).

v37.205  (v2.5)

  o You can now specify the Public Screen the requesters will appear on, if
    you do not specify one the requesters will appear on WorkBench.
    (Suggested by Klaus Alexander Seistrup)
  o Wait and Confirm requesters will now tell you the name of the icon they
    belong to.

v37.206  (v2.6)

  o Sort now works properly reguardless of case.

v37.207  (v2.7)

  o When running more than once, tempfile was not being unlocked.
    (Reported by Finn Kettner)

v37.208 (v2.8)

  o Was not freeing old tooltypes when using appicon, fixes problem of adding
    tooltypes to icons after first one was edited.

v37.210 (v2.10)

  o Swapped order of reading ENV variables, now ToolType will look for
    ENV:tooltype before ENV:editor.  This allows you to use a different editor
    for ToolType and more.
  o Added automatic commenting feature.  To comment out a tooltype, just place
    a ( at the begining and ToolType will automatically place the closing ). Or
    to uncomment a tooltype, just delete the opening ( and the closing ) will
    automatically be deleted.
  o Compiled with SAS C v6.50
  o ReqTools.library no longer included in archive, by now everyone has it.

v37.211 (v2.11)

  o Added locale support.  Includes CatComp sources.

v2.12  (v37.212)

  o Switched way versions will bre reported to conform to the RCS I started
    using.  From now on the '37' has been dropped and the decemil moved over
    one.   For example v37.212 is now v2.12, and what would have been v37.213
    will bee v2.13 as so on.
  o Add CTRLoC breaking to quit appicon.
  o Was checking for wrong error code on calls to Open() and Lock() (fixed)
  o Memory was not returned if an error occured saving icon (fixed)
  o Code cleaned up a bit.

v2.13

  o ToolType was not using the catalog string for the requester titles (fixed)
    Reported by Jerome Santini
  o Includes French and Danish catalogs.
  
v2.14

  o Changed default pattern in file requester from *.info to #?.info
    because not every one has * activated as a wildcard.
  o Fixed a small error in the Installer script
  o 'Save changes' requester will not appear if no changes were made to the temp
    file even if the option confirm is specified.  Suggested by Michael Nerone

v2.15

  o Tooltype will no longer remove the trailing ')' if '(' appears in the tooltype,
    this will alow you to use tooltypes that that require opening and closing
	parenthesis, such a file patterns.
  o Added File keyword (suggested by Andreas Schildbach)
    If you supply this option with the name of a text file with some tooltypes,
    ToolType will take these tooltypes and put them in the icon.  Note: the sorting
    options still work.  This is only available from the shell.
  o Catalog has changed.  Requires catalog for v2.15
@ENDNODE


